    a trt:Treatment .

<http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4762016>
    bibo:endPage "42" ;
    bibo:issue "4" ;
    bibo:journal "Illiesia" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2007-06-26" ;
    bibo:startPage "20" ;
    bibo:volume "3" ;
    dc:creator "McLellan, Ian D.; Zwick, Peter" ;
    dc:date "2007" ;
    dc:title "New Species Of And Keys To South American Gripopterygidae (Plecoptera)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758673>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758675>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758677>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758667>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758663>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758679>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4762020>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758683> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758673>
    dc:description "Figs. 43‐47. Early larval instars of Ceratoperla schwabei Illies (from a single sample from Chile, Malleco, Nahuelbuta, Los Gringos, 37°48ʹS, 73°01ʹW, 15‐17 December 1993, C&O Flint, Jr.; identified after Illies, 1963, fig. 36d, and Caamaño Mora, 1985, fig. 12). 43, first instar, habitus; 44 antenna of same; 45, combined ventral and dorsal views of segments 9 and 10; 46, detail of marginal hairs on tergite 10; 47, slightly larger specimen. Conspecificity of specimens was suggested by identical surface structure and body vestiture." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4758673/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758675>
    dc:description "Figs. 48‐49. Notoperla archiplatae (det. J. Illies, larva from Lo Valdes), late instar larva. 48, slightly oblique dorsal view of right half of fore body; 49, oblique anterior view of larval fore body from left side; note hair flanges on leg and along middorsal line. Arrow points at coxal projection; not to scale. c, coxa; cp, coxal projection; cy, clypeus; f, frons; la, labrum; t, trochanter." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4758675/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758677>
    dc:description "Figs. 50‐52. Antarctoperla altera Zwick, last instar larva. 50, habitus; 51, abdominal segment 10 and cerci, dorsal; 52, optical cross section through abdominal segment 7. Not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4758677/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758667>
    dc:description "Figs. 24‐29. Antarctoperlinae gen.sp. II, larva. 24, habitus; 25, detail of pronotal lateral margin; 26, hypopharynx, lateral; 27, same, dorsal; 28, rear part of an abdominal tergite, with surface pilosity and caudal setal fringe; 29, abdominal tip, lateral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4758667/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758663>
    dc:description "Figs. 18‐23. Antarctoperlinae gen.sp. I, larva.18, habitus; 19, left mandible, ventral; 20, left maxilla, ventral; 21, tarsus, lateral and dorsal; 22, lateral part of tergal hair fringe; 23, abdominal tip, ventral. Figs 19‐21 to same scale, 22‐23 not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4758663/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758679>
    dc:description "Figs. 53‐54. Fore bodies of last instar larvae of Rhithroperla cf. rossi Illies (53) and Limnoperla jaffueli (Navás) (54)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4758679/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4762020>
    dc:description "Figs. 61‐64. 61, Rhithroperla rossi, larval head; arrow marks prominent corners of clypeus. Pilosity on top of larval hind femur: Rhithroperla rossi (62), Teutoperla brundini (63), Limnoperla jaffueli (64); not to scale" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4762020/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758683>
    dc:description "Fig. 55‐60. Pilosity and chloride cells (57, 59; not to scale) in the paramedian area of tergite 8 of larval Claudioperla tigrina (55‐57), Rhithroperla rossi (58, 59) and Teutoperla brundini (60). Figures 56, 58, 59 are to same scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4758683/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

